==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weismannism
<hw>Weis"mann*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The theories and teachings in regard to heredity propounded by the
German biologist August <etsep>Weismann</etsep>, esp. in regard to germ
plasm as the basis of heredity and the impossibility of transmitting
acquired characteristics; -- often called
<altname>neo-Darwinism</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weiss beer</ent>⟦br⟧
